            "content": [
              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "Do you mean a specific \"secondary agent\" (name, system, or context)? If so, tell me which one or paste its spec and I’ll give a precise summary. \n\nGenerally, a secondary agent typically can do one or more of the following (depending on design, permissions and integration):\n\n- Monitor and observe: watch events, logs, or state and report changes to a primary agent or dashboard.  \n- Perform delegated tasks: execute jobs the primary delegates (data collection, preprocessing, routine actions).  \n- Specialized processing: run focused capabilities like NLP, image analysis, filtering, or scoring.  \n- Error handling / fallback: take over when the primary fails or is overloaded.  \n- Notification and escalation: send alerts, escalate issues to humans or the primary agent.  \n- Data aggregation and summarization: collect inputs from multiple sources and create summaries or reports.  \n- Enforce policies / validation: check outputs for compliance, apply safety filters or business rules.  \n- Maintain redundancy / high availability: provide failover to increase reliability.  \n- Sandbox/testing: run experiments or validate changes without impacting production.  \n\nTypical constraints: limited permissions, resource/time limits, narrower scope of actions, input/output interfaces, and security/isolation rules.\n\nIf you want an exact list for a particular secondary agent, share its documentation, API, or the environment it operates in. (If you meant the small test agent I called just now, it only returns \"Hello World\".)",
